BekreftelseSendtSøknad.SelvInformere: You must inform your employer yourself about when you will be away

BekreftelseSendtSøknad.ManglendeDokument: You are missing documentation to send us that we need to process your case. The documentation can be uploaded here under your case. After the documentation is sent, it usually takes about four weeks before the case is processed.
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.HuskÅInformere: Remember to inform your employer about how long you will be away from work, and whether you will be away full-time or part-time during the leave. Your employer will not get this information from Nav. If you change your leave plan, you must also remember to notify your employer.
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.HvisDuVilEndre: If you want to make changes to your plan
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.SendEndringssøkna: If you want to change your parental benefit plan, you can submit a change application by selecting change, available above your plan. Your changes will then be processed by Nav and you will receive a response with a new plan.
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.DuFårTidligstSvar: YOU WILL GET THE EARLIEST RESPONSE
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.TidligstSvarForkl: You can get the earliest response to your application 4 weeks before your first day of {erFp, select, true {parental benefit} other {pregnancy benefits}}. For the application to be processed, your employer must have submitted the income statement. This is because we use the most recent information about your income when calculating what you will receive in {erFp, select, true {parental benefit} other {pregnancy benefits}}.
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.FireUkerFør: Four weeks before your first day of {erFp, select, true {parental benefit} other {pregnancy benefits}}
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.NårDuFårSvar: When will you get a response to your application?
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.DuKanTidligstFåSv: You can get the earliest response to your application when you have submitted all necessary documentation in your case. You will receive a notification from us when the application is processed, and you can follow your case here.
When we have all necessary documentation, the expected processing time is 6 weeks.
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.NårUtbetalesPenge: When will the money be paid?
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.Utbetalingstidspu: You will usually receive the money 1 week after your application is approved.
on Nav's website you can see the payment on the evening of the day the money is paid.
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.VenterPåInntektsm: Your employer must send an income statement to us to tell us about your income. We must receive the income statement before we can process your application.
If you have multiple employers, they must all send their own income statements.
Your employer has received a notice on nav.no to send the income statement.
Your employer will receive a notice on nav.no when they can send the income statement.
The income statement can be sent earliest four weeks before your first day of parental benefit. This is because we need updated information about your income to calculate your parental benefit.
The income statement can be sent earliest four weeks before your first day of pregnancy benefits. This is because we need updated information about your income to calculate your pregnancy benefits.

BruktOpplysningerOmArbeidsforhold.tittel: Nav has retrieved information about your employment
The other parent has applied for parental benefit. For the other parent to receive parental benefit in certain periods, the regulations require that you are active, for example in work. In the application, the other parent has stated that you are working in one or more of these periods.

Nav has therefore retrieved information about your employment from the Employer and Employee Register (AA Register). We use the information when we process the application. We can also use the information for other periods in new applications. You can check what is registered about you in the AA Register (opens in a new tab).
We have done this under the National Insurance Act § 21-4. You can read more about the processing of personal data (opens in a new tab).
The regulations for activity requirements are in the National Insurance Act § 14-13. If you want to know more, you can find information on nav.no/parental-benefit (opens in a new tab).

inntektsmelding.spørsmål.hvaEr.tekst: In the income statement, your employer states what your usual salary is around the time you start your leave. The income statement is part of the basis Nav uses to calculate how much you will receive.

inntektsmelding.spørsmål.ikkeStemmer.tek: If you see something that is not correct, you must contact your employer. Your employer can then correct the error and send a new income statement to Nav. If the new income statement changes how Nav has calculated your income, you will receive a new decision.
